1. **`safeLabel` allows single-quote + double-hyphen → comment injection** (`lib/db/underlying-comps.ts:8`): The regex `/^[A-Za-z0-9 ,.\-/()+&']+$/` permits `'` and `--`. A value like `NYC'--` would pass validation and produce `"Market" = 'NYC'--'` — the `--` comments out the trailing quote and any remaining WHERE conditions. The impact is limited (read-only CSV, no destructive SQL possible) but this bypasses the rent-sanity guards in the WHERE clause. Compare to `safeDate()` in `duckdb.ts` which uses a strict allowlist with no special SQL characters.

